Ormat Technologies Inc. (ORA) â€™s unit
secured a contract with Norske Skog Tasman Ltd. of  New Zealand 
to supply a geothermal power plant.  The contract with Norske Skog, a manufacturer of pulp from
wood and other materials, is valued at about $20 million, Ormat
said in a statement yesterday.  The plant, to be constructed in the Kawerau Geothermal
Field in New Zealand, is expected to be completed within 13
months from the contract date, it said.  The Norske Skog plant is the 13th geothermal power plant
